    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Curious Cook column last Wednesday, about the chemistry of meat color, referred incorrectly to the chemical that binds with the pigment myoglobin to make nitrite-cured meat pink. It is nitric oxide (NO) -- not nitrous oxide (N2O), a sedative used in dentistry.</p>
      </block>
